				<header>
					<h1>Guidelines</h1>
					<p>The Members will be divided into two Main groups:</p>
<ul><li>
<b>Tech-hoppers</b>-(For those people who are interested in Tech news and related discussions only.)</li>
<li><b>Tech-holics</b>-(For those who are interested in learning and diving into programming and creating some really nice apps.)</li>
</ul>
				</header>
				<section>
					<p>Further Tech-holics will be sub-categorised into two categories:</p>
<ul><li><b>Newbies</b>- These will be working on Generating New Ideas for new and existing projects and will be following in the regular meet ups as per the schedule.</li>
<li><b>Dedicated</b>- Main role of this group will be blogging, Implementation of the New Ideas and projects, Managing the Deadline/Timeline for the projects being taken up and guiding Newbies with their Ideas.</li>
</ul>
<p>All the Member will be admitted as NEWBIE Initially and he/she has to complete the following criteria(s) to get Upgraded to the DEDICATED :</p>
<ol>
<li>At Least One of the Newbies' Ideas Should be Implemented.</li>
<li>Minimum Attendance in the Meet-Ups should not be less than 75%.</li>
<li>Should have Minimum of 1000 points on <a href="http://stackoverflow.com">STACKOVERFLOW</a>.</li>
</ol>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>Getting Started With us</h2>
					<ol>
						<li>Read all the Guidelines Before getting started.</li>
						<li>You need To create Accounts on the following sites:
							<ul>
								<li>Gmail</li>
								<li>StackOverflow</li>
								<li>Trello</li>
								<li>Github</li>
							</ul>
						</li>

						<li>Prefer Creating the Accounts on(Trello, stackOverflow,Github) with your same Gmail ID.</li>
				</section>

